  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine whether a new medical technology can temporarily
      alter pain perception. The new technology is called Transcranial direct current stimulation
      (tDCS).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Healthy subjects will complete questionnaires and undergo a laboratory pain assessment before
      and after a 20 minute session of real or sham tDCS.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
